      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAIRARAPA (7) chased gamely into the placings on debut at Illawarra Grange. Is sure to have come on from that and gets a key switch in Clark taking over. Expecting her to be more prominent this time and prove very tough to hold out. Her stablemate FARSET (1) shoulders a fitness edge and looked desperately close to breaking through before a flat effort last time. Backs up quickly and gets in well with the 2kg claim. Expect him to lead the way. SCOISH MALOISH (9) has progressed nicely in his last two and is open to further. Berry's booking is a good sign. SHARBINO (6) is rock-hard fit now and is drawn to get all the favours. Keeping safe for a minor spot.",
